  "name": "sensitivity-factors",
  "notes": "The relationship from every node to any branch in the network model is provided within the sensitivity factor tables. These are calculated using PSS/E load flow software and are used to determine the effect of increasing net demand at each node to net forward power flow along sensitive branches and the amount of curtailment required for any connection. \r\n\r\nPlease see the guidance document for further information.  \r\n\r\nhttps://dso.nationalgrid.co.uk/curtailment-analysis-data-usage-guidance\r\n\r\nTo reference between the bus numbers used in this data set and bus name used within the LTDS please see the [Bus Index](https://connecteddata.nationalgrid.co.uk/dataset/curtailment_buses)",
  "num_resources": 45,
  "num_tags": 6,
  "organization": {
    "id": "a65a370a-a123-4d90-bdb9-fb176c382e83",
    "name": "national_grid_electricity_distribution",
    "title": "National Grid Electricity Distribution",
    "type": "organization",
    "description": "## National Grid Electricity Distribution is the regional electricity distribution division of National Grid.\r\n\r\nFormerly known as Western Power Distribution, the UK\u2019s largest electricity distribution network serves nearly 8 million customers in the East and West Midlands, South West and Wales, delivering essential power to millions of homes and businesses across its regions.\r\n\r\nWith a distribution area of 550,000 square kilometres, it\u2019s 6,500 colleagues are committed to providing a safe, stable and reliable electricity supply and ensuring the highest quality of customer service.",
